Privacy Policy for Nervus
Last Updated: 15.09.2024

At Nervus, your privacy is of paramount importance to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our platform, Nervus, and the features supported by Gemini Justice.

By using Nervus, you consent to the practices described in this policy. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at contactnervus@gmail.com.

1. Information We Collect
To provide you with the best experience on Nervus, we collect several types of information, including:

1.1 Personal Information
Account Information: When you create an account, we collect your name, email address, and other profile information (such as a profile photo, if uploaded).
Communication Information: If you use our chat feature, we collect your messages, and Gemini helps moderate the conversation for community safety.
Leaderboard & Participation: We collect information about your participation in challenges and leaderboard rankings, including your captured moments of kindness.
1.2 Automatically Collected Information
Device Information: We may collect information about the device you use, such as device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.
Usage Data: This includes information on how you use Nervus, such as pages visited, features used, and the timing of your interactions with the app.
1.3 Content Submission
When you upload content (like images or stories about your acts of kindness), Gemini verifies and validates this content to ensure authenticity. The content is stored securely, and you decide when and how to share it.

2. How We Use Your Information
Nervus uses your information for the following purposes:

To Provide Our Service: We use your data to operate the Nervus platform, including user verification, leaderboard ranking, and content validation by Gemini.
To Personalize Your Experience: We use data to offer personalized suggestions for your next act of kindness and to connect you with relevant community discussions.
For Safety and Moderation: Gemini moderates the chat environment to maintain a safe and inclusive space for all users.
To Analyze and Improve: We analyze usage trends to improve Nervus, optimize performance, and introduce new functionalities.
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information in the following circumstances:

With Your Consent: When you choose to share your content with the community or participate in challenges, your information will be visible to others as part of the Nervus experience.
For Legal Purposes: We may share your information when required by law, such as complying with legal processes, regulatory requests, or protecting the rights and safety of users or the public.
Service Providers: We may use trusted third-party service providers to assist with operating Nervus (such as hosting services, analytics, or customer support). These providers are contractually obligated to maintain the confidentiality and security of the data.
4. Your Control Over Your Information
Profile Management: You can update or delete your personal information from your profile settings at any time.
Content Removal: You have full control over the moments of kindness you upload. You can choose to remove or edit your content at any time.
Data Requests: You can request access to, correction, or deletion of your personal data by contacting us at contactnervus@gmail.com.
5. Data Security
We implement robust technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse. These measures include encryption, firewalls, and secure access protocols. However, no system is 100% secure, and while we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. International Data Transfers
Your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in countries other than your own. We ensure that such transfers comply with applicable data protection laws, such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), by using standard contractual clauses or relying on the adequacy decisions of the European Commission where applicable.

7. Children's Privacy
Nervus is not intended for use by children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal data, we will promptly delete it. For users in the European Union, the minimum age for consent is 16, unless parental consent is provided.

8. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant updates through the app or by email, and your continued use of Nervus after such updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at contactnervus@gmail.com.

By using Nervus, you agree to this Privacy Policy. Thank you for being a part of our community and helping to spread kindness worldwide!
